{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_44","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Completion guard persistence**: the completion-blocked path still discards the only write that makes the run resumable.\nCurrent: [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L1500) sets `status = Failed` and `active_run = None`, but [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L1505) ignores `write_run_snapshot(...)` errors with `let _ = ...`. If that write fails, the last durable snapshot can remain non-resumable even though the command returns `CompletionBlocked`.\nExpected: do not swallow that persistence failure. Either durably write the resumable snapshot before returning `CompletionBlocked`, or surface a distinct snapshot-commit failure when that write cannot be persisted.\nReference: Loop 8 acceptance criterion: “if completion is otherwise ready but pending amendments are detected during terminalization, completion is blocked and the run remains resumable”.\n\n2. **Missing required final-review continuation coverage**: the mandated test coverage is still incomplete.\nCurrent: unit coverage exercises completion-panel continuation at [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L1874) and acceptance-QA continuation at [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L2053), while [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L2008) only proves the approved final-review happy path. The conformance feature file [run_completion_rounds.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_completion_rounds.feature#L1) likewise has no scenario where `final_review` returns `conditionally_approved` or `request_changes` and restarts planning.\nExpected: add unit and conformance coverage for final-review-driven continuation, including completion-round advancement and restart from `planning`.\nReference: Loop 8 acceptance criterion: “Conformance and unit coverage are added for ... final-review-driven continuation ...”.\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n- I could not rerun the Rust test suite locally because `cargo` is not installed in this environment. After the fixes above, rerun the targeted workflow-engine and conformance tests to confirm the late-stage state machine end to end."}}
